For God's sake, it must be worth it.

1208
02:41:01,707 --> 02:41:05,585
They're trying to force Urquhart
away from the river.

1209
02:41:05,669 --> 02:41:12,092
Now, once they do that, once they've got
him surrounded, he'll be annihilated.

1210
02:41:12,592 --> 02:41:15,512
Not in Monty's plan at all.

1211
02:41:15,595 --> 02:41:18,640
Have we replaced the boats
we lost at Nijmegen?

1212
02:41:20,058 --> 02:41:22,269
Yes.

1213
02:41:23,019 --> 02:41:25,105
Well?

1214
02:41:27,190 --> 02:41:29,276
Well, then?

1215
02:41:34,322 --> 02:41:37,367
That's it, then. We're pulling them out.

1216
02:41:43,832 --> 02:41:46,293
It was Nijmegen.

1217
02:41:46,376 --> 02:41:50,338
It was the single road...
getting to Nijmegen.

1218
02:41:50,422 --> 02:41:52,674
No, it was after Nijmegen.

1219
02:41:57,054 --> 02:42:00,307
And the fog. In England.

1220
02:42:04,895 --> 02:42:08,523
Doesn't matter what it was.
When one man says to another,

1221
02:42:08,607 --> 02:42:12,736
''I know what let's do today -
let's play the war game'',

1222
02:42:12,819 --> 02:42:15,322
everybody dies.

1223
02:42:18,200 --> 02:42:20,285
''Withdraw.''

1224
02:42:22,287 --> 02:42:25,415
Two days, they said.
We've been here nine.

1225
02:42:26,833 --> 02:42:31,338
One bloody mile -
you'd think they could accomplish that!

1226
02:42:31,421 --> 02:42:34,091
- Hancock, here are another two.
- Thank you.

1227
02:42:34,174 --> 02:42:37,552
- They're the last two I could find.
- Charles.

1228
02:42:38,762 --> 02:42:41,681
We've been given our marching orders.

1229
02:42:43,725 --> 02:42:46,937
If they discover we're leaving
they'll destroy us,

1230
